column5: Sure Table Rock, want to impress me, try that on simcoe in October. LOL  There was a thread earlier about if pro anglers were athletes, that seemed pretty athletic to me. hehe
I love it when he looks into the camera. WHAT IN THE LORD THUNDERN JESUS did i just do. Now thats dedication.
wow Rob...thats was some crazy stuff....would you do that on lake O in a salmon tourney?? A king would take you for a ride...lol
I saw Rob attempt that (involuntarily) in a Salmon tourney last summer. Good thing he didn't make the plunge....cuz they weren't about to stop the boat.
Now that's commitment to landing a fish no matter what happens!  LOL  Mike

To be the best you need that kind of intensity and focus... Ike would have done that on Simcoe in the fall if there was a tournament on the line. Worry about the cold after the fish is in the livewell.
It was even cooler when I posted it last week lol...Ahh I'm Just kidding with you, awesome video! -Ben
